You might often see programs use `using namespace std;` at the top.

This lets you write `cout` instead of `std::cout`.

```cpp
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
  cout << "Hello World!";
  return 0;
}
```
Both ways are completely fine, but using `std::cout` is often preferred in larger projects to avoid naming conflicts.
